Hey Kevin,

The mastic dampeners go on rather thick and it takes a bit of time for them 
to cure and dry out as they are installed in a thick layer. A week for full 
cure and dry out is about right. As the stuff dries, it gets a bit stiffer 
and supplies a little more damping.

Chris
